<sect1 id="_WARNING">
  <!-- DNT-Start --><title>#WARNING</title><!-- DNT-End -->

  <para><emphasis role="bold">#<!-- DNT-Start -->WARNING<!-- DNT-End --><indexterm>
      <primary>#<!-- DNT-Start -->WARNING<!-- DNT-End --></primary>
    </indexterm>( </emphasis><emphasis>message</emphasis> <emphasis
  role="bold">);</emphasis></para>

  <para><informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
      <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colwidth="77.10pt" />

        <colspec colwidth="275.70pt" />

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry><!-- DNT-Start --><emphasis>message</emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

            <entry>A string expression containing the warning message to
            display.</entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </informaltable></para>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold">#<!-- DNT-Start -->WARNING<!-- DNT-End --> </emphasis>statement displays the
  <emphasis>message </emphasis>in the workunit and/or syntax check. This
  statement may be used outside an <!-- DNT-Start -->XML<!-- DNT-End --> scope and does not require a previous
  <!-- DNT-Start -->LOADXML<!-- DNT-End --> to instantiate an <!-- DNT-Start -->XML<!-- DNT-End --> scope.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <!-- DNT-Start --><programlisting>  #IF(TRUE)
    #ERROR('broken');
    OUTPUT('broken');
  #ELSE
    #WARNING('maybe broken');
    OUTPUT('maybe broken');
  #END;
</programlisting><!-- DNT-End -->

  <para>See Also: <link linkend="_ERROR">#<!-- DNT-Start -->ERROR<!-- DNT-End --></link></para>
</sect1>
